<HL>
   Business Brief -- Glaverbel S.A.:
   Belgian Glass Maker Posts
   2% Rise in Profit for Half
</HL>
<DATE>
09/07/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   B.GLA J.AHG
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
CONTAINERS &amp; PACKAGING, BAGS, CANS, BOXES (CTR)
</IN>
<LP>
   Glaverbel S.A. of Belgium, a glass making affiliate of
Asahi Glass Co. of Japan, reported that first-half
consolidated profit rose 2% to 1.51 billion Belgian francs
($47.2 million) from 1.48 billion francs a year earlier.
   Revenue rose 4.7% to 13.95 billion francs from 13.32
billion francs.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Per-share earnings increased 3.5% to 317 francs from 306
francs.
</TEXT>
